verse_part: and out of the midst thereof
Also out of the midst thereof
and when those were lifted up
and he caused me to eat
of that which dieth of itself,
Yet will I leave a remnant,
that I should go far off
and when they were lifted up,
out of the midst of it.
wholly, [are] they unto whom the inhabitants
I have cast them far off
and they have made [others] to hope
Because, even because they have seduced
and upon them that have daubed
and I will cut him off
And they shall bear the punishment
to every one that passed by,
Thou hast played the whore also
yea, thou hast played the harlot with them,
with whom thou hast taken pleasure,
and all [them] that thou hast loved,
with all [them] that thou hast hated;
unto them, that they may see
and I will cause thee to cease
but, as [if that were] a very
in that thou art a comfort
And he went up and down
Wherefore I caused them to go forth
in that they caused to pass through
and shall I be enquired of
and shall be brought to pass,
Go thee one way or other,
that ye are come to remembrance,
And thou shalt take thine inheritance
as soon as she saw them
because thou hast gone a whoring
I will even make the pile
and I will cut thee off
and I will cause thee to perish
And they shall make a spoil
When I shall bring thee down
of the wares of thy making:
of the wares of thy making,
that they can hide from thee:
thou hast walked up and down
therefore I will cast thee as profane
and I will bring thee up
yet shalt thou be brought down
and they shall bring thee up
when I shall put thee out,
of that whereof it was full,
And when this cometh to pass,
And I will bring them out
will cause them to lie down,
and I will make myself known
I will also cause [you] to dwell
And I will turn thee back,
It shall also come to pass,
to them that are at rest,
And it shall come to pass
And I will turn thee back,
and leave but the sixth part of thee,
and will cause thee to come up
And it shall come to pass
that I might shew [them] unto thee
Now when he had made an end
And [it was] according to the appearance
When thou hast made an end
by the way of the same.
to do the office of a priest
And it shall come to pass,
with any thing that causeth sweat.
nor her that is put away:
that he may cause the blessing
Moreover, when ye shall divide by lot
And a [portion shall be] for the prince
and ye shall give the sixth part
and according to the meat offering,
and caused me to pass by
And it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass,
it shall bring forth new fruit
And it shall come to pass,
And it shall come to pass,
